sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Test Client
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant TrainOp as Training Operator
    participant KubeRay as KubeRay Operator
    participant Kueue as Kueue Controller
    participant Workers as Worker Pods<br/>(Training/Ray Images)
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Pod<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 1: Distributed PyTorch Training (KFTO)
    Client->>K8sAPI: Create PyTorchJob CR<br/>HTTPS/6443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>TrainOp: Notify (watch event)<br/>Internal, RBAC
    TrainOp->>Workers: Create Worker Pods<br/>Internal, ServiceAccount
    Workers->>Workers: NCCL Rendezvous<br/>TCP/29500, plaintext
    Workers->>S3: Upload/Download Model<br/>HTTPS/443, AWS IAM

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: Ray Cluster Job Submission
    Client->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster CR<br/>HTTPS/6443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>KubeRay: Notify (watch event)<br/>Internal, RBAC
    KubeRay->>RayHead: Create Ray Head Pod<br/>Internal, ServiceAccount
    RayHead->>Workers: Connect Ray Workers<br/>TCP/6379,10001, plaintext
    Client->>RayHead: Submit Job via Dashboard<br/>HTTP/8265, No Auth
    Client->>RayHead: GET /api/jobs/{jobID}<br/>HTTP/8265, No Auth
    RayHead-->>Client: Job Status/Logs

    Note over Client,Prom: Flow 3: Kueue Workload Admission
    Client->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster with queue-name label<br/>HTTPS/6443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Kueue: ValidatingAdmissionPolicy check<br/>Internal, Admission webhook
    Kueue->>Kueue: Evaluate ClusterQueue/LocalQueue<br/>Internal, RBAC
    Kueue-->>K8sAPI: Workload admitted/rejected

    Note over Client,Prom: GPU Metrics Collection
    Client->>Prom: Query GPU utilization (DCGM)<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer Token
    Prom-->>Client: Metrics response
